  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Phase shift treatment is a new tinnitus therapy that aims at sound cancelling via complete or
      partial residual inhibition. This technique is based on the theory by Choy advocating that
      the induction of a sound wave with a 180 degree phase shift compared to the sound experienced
      by the patient could result in sound cancelling, likely by negation of the cortical
      perception of tinnitus.

      The aim is to determine the efficacy of the Phase Out treatment in pure tone and narrow band
      noise tinnitus patients.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
